  "texts": [
    "While some focused on encoding the geometric coordinates, others were better suited for the compression of the associated attributes such as colors.",
    "Since color attributes are usually required to enable human visualization, both classes of algorithms have to be combined to allow the data to be completely represented.",
    "Compression methods can also be grouped according to the underlying algorithm.",
    "For instance, some techniques project 3D models onto multiple planes and encode their projections as regular images.",
    "Other methods compress geometry and attributes directly in their original spatial domain."
  ],
